main event: An observation of a falling object towards the earth burning bright blue and making a hissing sound on 14 Mar 61.
interesting points: The object was observed for 60 seconds as it fell towards earth., The object was described as bright blue and giving off sparks., Witnesses made no specific mention of the object's trajectory or altitude., The report speculates that it may have been a meteor, aircraft, or astronomical object., Detailed coordinates suggest the object was approximately 23-25 miles away from the observer.
sighted object: one falling object burning bright blue
